title: PPPP Candidate Sardar Sanaullah Zehri wins PB-18 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peopleâ€™s Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) candidate Sardar Sanaullah Zehri has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-18, Khuzdaar by securing 20,014 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI) candidate Ghulam Sarwar who bagged 13,791 votes.
Voters turnout remained 55.50 percent.
